vision.en-US: At SlayFit Vili shows a mixture of movements and mindset. We don't need to punish the body for this to work, a little everyday goes a long way.

philosophySubtitle.en-US: Mindset and body transformed - Be fabulously fit!

content.value: Coming to SlayFitVili, we work out - that's correct.
But guess what, you will shape not only your body, but your mind, and the quality of life.
Moving with purpose, building confidence, and showing up as your best self. We believe showing up is already 50% of the process.
A good health and fierce body don't just come from the gym, it comes also from the kitchen and your sleep. Vili makes sure they all get the necessary attention.

Vili is not just your coach, he is your cheerleader, your mindset consultant, your gym buddy and a good company health-wise. He guides you with knowledge, logic, and purpose, so none of your time and effort will go to waste.
You’ll feel inspired to love yourself more by showing up, doing your best, and making steady progress day by day, week by week.
Are you ready to step into your power? Let’s slay.

question.en-US: What’s the best way to lose weight?

content.value: There is no magic trick. The key is creating a sustainable calorie deficit—burning more energy than you take in.
Combine smart nutrition with regular physical activity
Sleep, stress, and consistency matter more than any “fat-burning” trick

question.en-US: Do I need to cut carbs to lose weight?

content.value: No. Carbs are not the enemy.
total calorie intake less than calories out
Carbs are your body’s main energy source—especially for training
Instead of cutting carbs, focus on

question.en-US: How fast should I lose weight?

content.value: Slow and steady wins the race.

question.en-US: Why am I not losing weight even though I eat healthy and only eat 2 meals/day?

content.value: “Healthy” doesn’t always mean “low-calorie.” Less meals does not matter. What matters is the quality of the food you eat in each meal.
You may still be eating more calories than you burn
Portion sizes, snacks, and drinks add up

question.en-US: Can I lose fat in just one area (like the belly)?

content.value: Targeted training strengthens muscles but doesn’t control where fat comes off
Combine full-body training with smart nutrition for best results

question.en-US: How do I build muscle effectively?

content.value: Train with resistance and gradually increase intensity
and rest days—muscles grow during recovery

question.en-US: How much protein do I need per day?

content.value: 1.6–2.2 g of protein per kg of body weight
like eggs, meat, dairy, tofu, legumes
More protein doesn’t always mean more gains—balance matters

question.en-US: Do I need supplements to gain muscle?

content.value: is safe and well-researched—it helps increase strength and muscle volume

question.en-US: Why am I training hard but not gaining muscle?

content.value: Inconsistent effort or not tracking progress

question.en-US: Can I build muscle and lose fat at the same time?

content.value: Yes, but it depends on your starting point.
Beginners or people returning after a break can do both
It’s slower than doing one goal at a time but very possible with the right plan

question.en-US: Is eating after 6 PM bad for fat loss?

content.value: meal timing doesn’t cause weight gain
matters more than when you eat
Eating late isn’t a problem unless it leads to mindless snacking or overconsumption

question.en-US: Do I need to detox or do juice cleanses?

content.value: No. Your body already has built-in detox organs:
drink water, eat real food, and move your body

question.en-US: Are fats bad for you?

content.value: for hormones, brain function, and nutrient absorption.
from sources like nuts, olive oil, avocados, and fatty fish
Balance is key—don’t overdo any one macronutrient

question.en-US: Do carbs make you fat?

content.value: Carbs fuel your training and support recovery
(like oats, rice, potatoes, fruit), not ultra-processed ones

question.en-US: Is it true that eating small meals speeds up metabolism?

content.value: Meal frequency has little to no effect on metabolism.
Your metabolism won’t “shut down” from skipping a meal

question.en-US: Will lifting weights make me bulky?

content.value: it takes years of focused effort, top-tier high protein consistent diets, and hormones to build big muscle mass
One kilogram of fat is 3 times bigger than one kilograms of muscle, so losing fat and gaining muscles will make you look toned and even slimmer/fitter.

question.en-US: Do women need different workouts than men?

content.value: are the same: squat, push, pull, hinge
—many women prefer glutes, core, and posture work

question.en-US: Can I train during my period?

content.value: Always listen to your body; rest when needed, push when ready

question.en-US: Do I need to eat less than 1,200 calories to lose weight?

content.value: Eating too little can slow your metabolism, drain energy, and disrupt hormones
more effective and healthier long term

question.en-US: Is sweating more = burning more fat?

content.value: Nope. Sweat is just your body’s way of
Fat loss comes from calorie deficit
Some great workouts may not leave you drenched—and that’s okay

question.en-US: Should I only do cardio to lose weight?

content.value: cardio alone won’t shape your body
a mix of cardio, strength, and smart eating

question.en-US: Should women train based on their body shape (pear, apple, hourglass, etc.)?

content.value: Body shape is mostly genetic. Training can improve your physique, but it can’t “reshape” your skeleton or target fat loss in one area.
Spot reduction is a myth—fat loss happens across the whole body, not just where you train most.
For most beginners, the priority should be building overall strength and muscle mass. Without that foundation, trying to specialize too early leads to poor results.
Training by body type often promotes unbalanced routines and ignores what your body actually needs to progress.
The most effective strategy? Full-body training that builds strength, improves posture, and supports long-term results—regardless of body shape.
Start with the fundamentals. The shape you’re aiming for comes from consistency, not shortcuts.

question.en-US: Is whey protein unnatural or harmful?

content.value: whey protein is a natural byproduct of milk
Great for meeting protein needs when food alone falls short

question.en-US: Do I need supplements to get fit?

content.value: You can reach your goals with
real food, smart training, and consistency

question.en-US: Is creatine only for men or bodybuilders?

content.value: creatine is one of the most researched and safe supplements for everyone
Safe for long-term use in healthy individuals

Should I take a multivitamin?

content.value: If your diet lacks variety, a
basic multivitamin can help cover gaps
Always aim for nutrients from various food sources first, supplements second

question.en-US: What is a Training Plan?

content.value: A training plan is a combination of diagnosis of a client's health status, ie level of fitness in different aspects (flexibility, strength, power, durability, balance …), training history and training goals, and most importantly a workout plan with specific exercises to target the clients’ needs and improve weaknesses.

question.en-US: What is included in the Training Plan?

content.value: Exercise selection based on your goals & fitness level

question.en-US: Why is a training plan important?

content.value:
Provides Direction & Purpose – Ensures every workout has a clear goal rather than random exercises.
Enhances Efficiency – Maximizes results by following a structured approach instead of wasting time on ineffective workouts.
Tracks Progress – Helps measure improvements in strength, endurance, and fitness over time.
Prevents Plateaus – Adapts training to keep you challenged and progressing.
Reduces Risk of Injury – Ensures balanced workouts, proper recovery and prevents overtraining

question.en-US: What is the EAT BETTER, LIVE BETTER package (Dietary guidance)?

content.value: The package consists of the dietary guidance, which determines the amount of calories, protein, fat, and carbs a person needs to achieve a goal (lose or gain weight with the best muscle results), and will be customized to fit a person’s wants and lifestyle.
Dietary Guidance program includes daily check-ins with your coach via WhatsApp, where you can:
✔️ Share meal photos and discuss food choices

This guidance will ensure that the client will accumulate sufficient knowledge after 12 weeks of guidance to be able to make dieting decisions on their own.

title.en-US: I never knew I could succeed in dieting - Long lasting dieting skill

content.value: I was inspired by Vili's body transformation, that's why I came to Vili for coaching. I was curious because I had tried dieting before, but I never succeeded.

Vili coached me with daily messages, clear and, comprehensive instructions. He answered the messages always instantly. During the period of 4 months, I slowly but steadily lost weight, around 17kg. I learned new knowledge, tips, and dieting tricks every day.

I tried many "special" diet hacks and trends before, but only when working with Vili that I realize: it doesn't need to be hard, suffering, or stressful at all - you only need to learn the right way, the right amount to eat. I enjoy life quite the same, if not more, with the new healthy lifestyle. Even now, as a flight attendant with a hectic life and diverse food sources, I still manage to eat healthy with the knowledge I learned.

After that, I challenged myself further by starting to hit the gym, and Vili had a way for a softie beginner in the gym like me. Now I slowly build a new habit of exercising, and my energy and health steadily increases day by day.
I cannot recommend Vili much enough. Such a life-changing experience.
